{{Infobox Radar |name= Aistyonok |image= Aistenok radar maks2009.jpg |caption= Aistyonok on display in 2009 |country= {{RUS}} |introdate= |number= |type= [[Counter-battery radar]] |frequency= |range= {{convert|20|km|sp=us}} |altitude= <!--{{m to ft|X|addr=yes}}--> |diameter= <!--{{m to ft|X|addr=yes}}--> |azimuth= |elevation= |precision= <!--±{{m to ft|X|addr=yes}}--> |power= |Developed By=[[Almaz-Antey]]}}
'''Aistyonok''' ({{lang-ru|Аистёнок}}, ''[[Stork]]''; [[GRAU]] designation '''1L271''') is a [[Counter-battery radar]] system developed and produced by [[Almaz-Antey]] for the [[Russian Armed Forces]]. It is a mobile [[radar]] for the purpose of detecting position of fire weapons such as [[field artillery]] and [[anti-aircraft warfare|anti-aircraft weapons]], calculating the [[trajectory]] of incoming [[Artillery shell|shells]], and the control of [[unmanned aerial vehicles]]. Aistyonok can detect moving ground targets at a distance of up to {{convert|20|km|sp=us}}, with capabilities to detect [[Mortar (weapon)|mortar]] fire positions at a distance of up to {{convert|5|km|sp=us}}, moving ground equipment at a distance of up to {{convert|20|km|sp=us}}, and the adjustment of artillery fire from {{convert|5|km|sp=us}} to {{convert|15|km|sp=us}} depending on the conditions.<ref>https://www.armyrecognition.com/weapons_defence_industry_military_technology_uk/artillery_units_of_the_russian_southern_military_district_to_operate_aistyonok_man-portable_radar_tass_12212161.html </ref>
The Aistyonok system was debuted in 2008, and has since been introduced for limited use in the [[North Caucasus]] by the Russian Armed Forces.
